'''Antonio Eromonsele Nordby Nusa''' (born 17 April 2005) is a Norwegian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] or [[attacking midfielder]] for {{German football updater|RBLeipzi}} club [[RB Leipzig]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]]. He's been described by many as one of the most exciting young prospects in world football.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-05-13 |title=From Yamal to Guler, Maino and Yildiz – the 20 best talents in world football| url=https://telegrafi.com/en/from-Yamal-to-Guler-Maino-and-Yildiz%2C-the-20-best-talents-in-world-football-at-the-moment/ |website=Telegrafi |language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250319213518/https://telegrafi.com/en/from-Yamal-to-Guler-Maino-and-Yildiz%2C-the-20-best-talents-in-world-football-at-the-moment/|archive-date=19 March 2025}}</ref>

==Club career==
Starting his career at [[Langhus IL|Langhus]], he moved to [[Stabæk Fotball|Stabæk]]'s youth section at the age of 13.<ref name=nff>{{NFF|3125744}}</ref> He signed his first professional contract with Stabæk in May 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-05-13 |title=Sportssjefen med et stort håp for sin første proffsignering |url=https://www.stabak.no/nyheter/sportssjefen-med-et-stort-hap-for-sin-forste-proffsignering |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210922142941/https://www.stabak.no/nyheter/sportssjefen-med-et-stort-hap-for-sin-forste-proffsignering |archive-date=2021-09-22 |access-date=2024-06-25 |website=Stabæk |language=no |url-status=live}}</ref>

He was given the chance to train with the senior team in early 2021,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-02-25 |title=- Skal lage kaos i forsvaret |url=https://www.stabak.no/nyheter/skal-lage-kaos-i-forsvaret |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416024606/https://www.stabak.no/nyheter/skal-lage-kaos-i-forsvaret |archive-date=2021-04-16 |access-date=2024-06-25 |website=Stabæk |language=no |url-status=live}}</ref> and subsequently given a new three-year contract in May of that year.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.stabak.no/nyheter/nusa-en-stor-dag-i-dag-ogsa|title=Nusa: "En stor dag i dag også"|date=6 May 2021|publisher=Stabæk Fotball|language=no|access-date=20 May 2021}}</ref> On 30 May 2021, he made his [[Eliteserien]] debut against [[Rosenborg BK|Rosenborg]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-05-30 |title=Kamp: Rosenborg |url=https://www.stabak.no/lag/import/tournament/eliteserien-2021/season/fotballsesongen-2021/match/round-6-rosenborg-x-stabaek |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240625092815/https://www.stabak.no/lag/import/tournament/eliteserien-2021/season/fotballsesongen-2021/match/round-6-rosenborg-x-stabaek |archive-date=2024-06-25 |access-date=2024-06-25 |website=Stabæk |language=no}}</ref> On 27 June 2021, he scored his first goal for the club in a 4–1 defeat against [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-06-27 |title=NUSA ETTER PRAKTSCORING: - Jeg ble litt sjokkert |url=https://www.stabak.no/nyheter/nusa-etter-praktscoring-jeg-ble-litt-sjokkert |access-date=2024-06-25 |website=Stabæk |language=no}}</ref> He made his full debut three days later, scoring two goals against [[Viking FK]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-06-27 |title=Nusa fra start |url=https://www.stabak.no/nyheter/nusa-fra-start |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240625092653/https://www.stabak.no/nyheter/nusa-fra-start |archive-date=2024-06-25 |access-date=2024-06-25 |website=Stabæk |language=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-06-30 |title=Nusa stjal showet i seksmålsthriller |url=https://www.stabak.no/nyheter/nusa-stjal-showet-i-thriller |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240625092827/https://www.stabak.no/nyheter/nusa-stjal-showet-i-thriller |archive-date=2024-06-25 |access-date=2024-06-25 |website=Stabæk |language=no}}</ref>

During the last transfer day of summer 2021, he signed a contract with [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]]. On 13 September 2022, he scored a goal on his [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut in a 4–0 away win against [[FC Porto|Porto]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.in/football/report?gameId=652606 |title=Brugge shock Porto with 4-0 away triumph |website=ESPN |date=13 September 2022 }}</ref> becoming the youngest Norwegian player to feature, and the second youngest player of any nationality to score in the competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/025a-0e9f8a869d0f-4945c17a2380-1000--champions-league-youngest-goalscorers-antonio-nusa-into-top-ten/ |title=Champions League youngest goalscorers: Antonio Nusa into top ten |website=UEFA |date=13 September 2022 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=2022-09-13 |title=Champions League youngest goalscorers: Antonio Nusa into top ten |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/025a-0e9f8a869d0f-4945c17a2380-1000--champions-league-youngest-goalscorers-antonio-nusa-into-top-ten/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221102225450/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/025a-0e9f8a869d0f-4945c17a2380-1000--champions-league-youngest-goalscorers-antonio-nusa-into-top-ten/ |archive-date=2022-11-02 |access-date=2024-06-25 |website=UEFA |language=en |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Friberg |first1=Jens |last2=Hellenes |first2=Andreas |last3=Folvik |first3=Herman |date=2022-09-13 |title=Drømmekveld for Club Brügges Antonio Nusa (17): Scoret da han ble tidenes yngste nordmann i Champions League |url=https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/P49WGJ/droemmekveld-for-club-brugges-antonio-nusa-17-scoret-da-han-ble-tidenes-yngste-nordmann-i-champions-league |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240625092843/https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/P49WGJ/droemmekveld-for-club-brugges-antonio-nusa-17-scoret-da-han-ble-tidenes-yngste-nordmann-i-champions-league |archive-date=2024-06-25 |access-date=2024-06-25 |website=VG |language=no}}</ref>

On 13 August 2024, Nusa signed a five-year contract with [[RB Leipzig]] in Germany.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=RB Leipzig|url=https://rbleipzig.com/news/2024-2025/antonio-nusa-rb-leipzig-transfer-neuzugang-rbl-offensive-saison-2024-25/|title=Antonio Nusa verstärkt RB Leipzig|trans-title=Antonio Nusa strengthens RB Leipzig|date=13 August 2024|access-date=13 August 2024|language=de|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240813182759/https://rbleipzig.com/news/2024-2025/antonio-nusa-rb-leipzig-transfer-neuzugang-rbl-offensive-saison-2024-25/|archive-date=13 August 2024}}</ref> Later that month, on 24 August, he scored a goal on his [[Bundesliga]] debut in a 1–0 victory over [[VfL Bochum]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportschau.de/fussball/bundesliga/nusa-schiesst-leipzig-zum-auftaktsieg,bundesliga-rbl-boc-100.html |title=Neuzugang Nusa schießt Leipzig zum Auftaktsieg |publisher=Sportschau |language=de |date=26 August 2024 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Norway Italy - June 2025 C 21.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Nusa (left) with [[Erling Haaland|Haaland]] celebration with [[Norway national football team|Norway]] in 2025]]

Nusa was called up by the [[Norway national under-19 football team|Norway U19s]] for the [[2023 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualification|elite qualifying round]] for the [[2023 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]], and scored the winner in a 2–1 win over [[France national under-19 football team|France]] in [[Orléans]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.footnews.be/news/363421/le-but-sublime-dantonio-nusa-face-a-lequipe-de-france-u19-video |title=Le but sublime d'Antonio Nusa face à l'Equipe de France U19 |website=footnews.be |date=26 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230401155147/https://www.footnews.be/news/363421/le-but-sublime-dantonio-nusa-face-a-lequipe-de-france-u19-video|archive-date=1 April 2023}}</ref>

In August 2023, Nusa received his first call-up to the [[Norway national football team|Norway senior national team]] by head coach [[Ståle Solbakken]], for a [[Exhibition game#International football|friendly match]] against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]] and a [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group A|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] match against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Norges tropp mot Jordan og Georgia |trans-title=Norway's squad against Jordan and Georgia |url=https://www.fotball.no/landslag/norge-a-herrer/2023/norges-tropp-mot-jordan-og-georgia/|website=[[Norwegian Football Federation]]|date=29 August 2023|access-date=2 September 2023|language=no}}</ref> He scored his first international goal for Norway in his debut match against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]], which they won by 6–0.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Sebastian|last=Stafford-Bloor|title=Who is Tottenham transfer target Antonio Nusa? Meet the next big thing out of Norway|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5213975/2024/01/20/tottenham-antonio-nusa/|website=[[The Athletic]]|date=19 January 2024|access-date=20 January 2024|url-access=subscription|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240909075752/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5213975/2024/01/20/tottenham-antonio-nusa/|archive-date=9 September 2024}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Unlike many wingers who struggle when switched flanks, Nusa is equally effective on both wings. Renowned for his explosive pace and direct playing style, he offers a significant threat on the counter-attack. His technical ability and flair have earned him the nickname "Norwegian Neymar."<ref>{{cite web |last=V |first=Sanjay Kumar |date=17 June 2025 |title=Antonio Nusa to Arsenal: Scout Report + SWOT Analysis |url=https://soccersouls.com/antonio-nusa-to-arsenal-scout-report-swot-analysis/ |access-date=17 June 2025 |website=Soccersouls|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260411170611/https://soccersouls.com/antonio-nusa-to-arsenal-scout-report-swot-analysis/|archive-date=11 April 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Nusa was born in Norway to a Norwegian mother and [[Nigeria]]n father.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Ifeanyi|last=Emmanuel|title=3 goals in 4 senior games: 16-year-old Stabaek winger could spark tug-of-war between Nigeria & Norway|url=https://www.allnigeriasoccer.com/read_news.php?nid=40338|website=All Nigeria Soccer|date=2 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240421201515/https://www.allnigeriasoccer.com/read_news.php?nid=40338|archive-date=21 April 2024}}</ref>

